Carter Name Meaning in English

What does the name Carter mean? What is the meaning of the name Carter, lucky number, lucky stone, origin and religion.

Carter is a family name, and also may be a given name. Carter is of Irish, Scottish and English origin and is an occupational name given to one who transports goods by cart or wagon originally believed to be of Gaelic and Celtic origins and a possible form of the name McCarter.

Carter Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Cart driver Short Info: Historically a surname, Carter has since become a name in its own right. Carter is famously the family name of bestselling musical couple Beyonc� and Jay Z, whose full names are Beyonc� Giselle Knowles-Carter and Shawn Corey Carter. The 1971 and 2000 films 'Get Carter' focus on gangster Jack Carter. Details: From the surname Carter, which was an occupational name for someone who transported goods. Believed to originally derive from the Latin carrum, meaning "carrier".
